    * The **food and beer** in Indy is great and plentiful. If you're in Broad Ripple, there are 3 separate microbreweries within 1,000 feet of each other ([Three Wisemen](https://www.thr3ewisemen.com/), [Brugge Brasserie](https://www.bruggebrasserie.com/), [Broad Ripple Brew Pub](https://www.broadripplebrewpub.com/)) and that's just Broad Ripple. (See [Brewers Of Indiana Guild](https://drinkin.beer/breweries/). Also, NY Times article [In Indianapolis, the World Comes to Eat](https://www.nytimes.com/2011/02/23/dining/23united.html?pagewanted=all).)
    * If family is your thing, the towns around Indianapolis are consistently ranked in the top 100 of best places to live. (See [Carmel](https://money.cnn.com/magazines/moneymag/bplive/2010/snapshots/PL1810342.html), [Fishers](https://money.cnn.com/magazines/moneymag/bplive/2010/snapshots/PL1823278.html), [Westfield](https://money.cnn.com/magazines/moneymag/bplive/2011/snapshots/PL1882700.html), [Noblesville](https://money.cnn.com/magazines/moneymag/bplive/2011/states/IN.html), [Brownsburg](https://money.cnn.com/magazines/moneymag/bplive/2011/snapshots/PL1808416.html), [Zionsville](https://money.cnn.com/galleries/2008/fsb/0803/gallery.best_places_to_launch.fsb/57.html), and [Plainfield](https://money.cnn.com/magazines/moneymag/bplive/2011/snapshots/PL1860246.html).)
    * The state is in strong **financial health** and has become a model for other states in the region. You're not getting that in California, or even Illinois. (See [CNN](https://money.cnn.com/2011/02/14/news/economy/mitch_daniels_indiana_state_budget/index.htm))

